Hoist mutations to a typed reducer + useOptimistic in the list. Pseudocode for StudioListView.tsx onStatusChange path:

```tsx
// In PostStudioPanel.tsx (parent owns the optimistic layer):
const [optimisticDrafts, applyOptimistic] = useOptimistic(
  drafts,
  (state, patch: {id: string; status?: string; scheduledAt?: string}) =>
    state.map(d => d.id === patch.id ? {...d, ...patch} : d)
);
const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

const onStatusChange = (id: string, next: string) => {
  startTransition(async () => {
    applyOptimistic({id, status: next});           // pill flips NOW
    const {error} = await supabase.from('carousel_drafts')
      .update({status: next}).eq('id', id);
    if (error) { toastError('update status', error); return; } // useOptimistic auto-reverts on throw inside transition
    await refresh();
  });
};

// In CarouselEditor.tsx — replace setBusy entirely:
const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();
async function run(fn, successMsg) {
  startTransition(async () => {
    try { await fn(); toast.success(successMsg); onChanged(); }
    catch (err) { toastError('action', err); }
  });
}
// Buttons read isPending instead of busy === 'schedule'. Note: useTransition
// auto-batches and won't block the input thread — currently every setBusy
// triggers a synchronous re-render of the entire 3-column editor.
```

This also kills the `setEditingStatusId(null)` race in StudioListView.tsx:531-533 — the select closes before the server confirms, but the row would briefly snap back to the old status if the mutation failed. With useOptimistic the rollback is automatic.

Pick one canonical surface per transition class.
- USER-INITIATED (Ivan clicked Approve): toast OFF, pill morph ON (the click target IS the focus), card swap ON. Skip row-flash since the user is in the editor sheet.
- SYSTEM-INITIATED (generation finished, status changed via polling): toast ON (because Ivan is probably in another tab), row-flash ON, pill morph ON. Skip card swap (the editor may not even be open).

